    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="405"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659.119/362k</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>926. The Danish commissioners have had a series of conferences with the War Trade
                    Board who have been very favorably impressed with the personnel of the
                    commission. The War Trade Board, during these conferences, have adhered to the
                    terms of the proposal of January 17.<note n="2" xml:id="d405fn2">See telegram
                        No. 6297, Jan. 19, 1918, to the Ambassador in Great Britain, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1299">p. 1299</ref>.</note>
                    The Legation will be kept informed of any new developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
